        <speech by="#bbf5376f-1a5e-4a10-ac71-5a195ac61a59">
          <from>MR. ANDREW YOUNGER</from>
          <p>MR. ANDREW YOUNGER : Mr. Speaker, my question is for the Premier. Will the Premier explain why his government decided to endorse the portion of the rate settlement with Nova Scotia Power that increases rates for the next two years and piles on additional costs in future years for further increases?</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#0768c045-71ae-4890-b6be-c52eb783ee95">
          <from>THE PREMIER</from>
          <p>THE PREMIER : Mr. Speaker, we are interested in only one thing and that is the lowest and fairest rates, unlike the Liberal Party who is pursuing or would pursue deregulation that would drive up the cost of electricity to ordinary families, people who are trying to make ends meet, by 30 to 50 per cent.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#bbf5376f-1a5e-4a10-ac71-5a195ac61a59">
