        <speech by="#41fa6a70-397a-4597-900b-20b957bef948">
          <from>MR. LEO GLAVINE</from>
          <p>MR. LEO GLAVINE : Mr. Speaker, recent media reports have many people shaking their heads. While government will pay for the drugs necessary to keep palliative care patients at home, they do not pay for the nutritional therapy replacement - in other words, their food. While the nutritional therapy is available in hospital, it's not covered for those who have chosen to take their loved ones home to die. Could the minister please explain how this makes any sense?</p>
